**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** [Insert Vehicle Make/Model]
**VIN:** [Insert VIN Number]
**Date of Inspection:** [Insert Date]

**Location of Damage:**
The rear fender of the vehicle shows visible damage. The damage appears to be a scratch or dent located on the lower portion of the rear fender, near the wheel well.

**Type of Damage:**
The damage seems to be a superficial scratch or dent, likely caused by an impact with another object or a curb. There is no indication of significant structural damage, such as a buckle or deformation of the metal.

**Additional Notes:**
- The scratch/dent is linear and does not appear to extend into the body panel.
- The paint around the area of damage looks intact without any signs of peeling or chipping.
- No other visible damage is noted on the rear fender or surrounding areas.

**Conclusion:**
The rear fender has sustained a minor scratch or dent that requires attention but does not necessitate immediate repair. Further inspection may be needed if the scratch/dent is deep enough to affect the structural integrity of the fender.
